    "### Type and Range Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "Data validation is the process of ensuring that data is accurate and of high quality. It is a critical first step in any data processing workflow. Type and range validation are two of the most common types of validation. Type validation ensures that the data is of the correct type (e.g., integer, string), while range validation ensures that the data is within a valid range (e.g., age between 0 and 120)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def validate_age(x):","    try:","        v = int(x)","        return v if 0 <= v <= 120 else None","    except Exception:","        return None","print([validate_age(a) for a in ['25','-1','x','200']])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Activity:** Write `validate_score(x)` returning `None` unless `0 <= int(x) <= 100`. Apply to a list."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def validate_score(x):\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        score = int(x)\n",
    "        return score if 0 <= score <= 100 else None\n",
    "    except (ValueError, TypeError):\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "\n",
    "scores = ['85', '101', '70', 'invalid', '-5']\n",
    "validated_scores = [validate_score(s) for s in scores]\n",
    "print(validated_scores)"
   ]
  },
